    <note>Ren(1) Zhongzheng [875] There were three lineage branches (jia) of the Lean jun Ren(1) during the Song--1} the Jiyin zu, 2} the Luoyang zu (lineage uncle=Bu [882] (q.v.), and 3} the Wenyang zu). Zhongzheng was a member of the wealthy Jiyin zu. He was Zhongxing's [876] elder brother, Zhongshi's [877] brother. Liang(1) Gu(1)'s [1135] father-in-law. A nephew Yuanqing [3431] was Wen(2) Yanbo's [1953] son-in-law. Zhongzheng was a member of Ding(1) Wei's [1641] coalition. When Chen(1) Yi [55] was transferred from Hebei yunshi to Shanxi yunshi, he recommended that Zhongzheng replace him (zidai). Zhongzheng was then appointed Jiangnan yunfu. Li(2) Bing's [8082] father-in-law, Ren(1) Li [3429], was a probable descendant. Zhang Fangping, WJ, 39.37b; XCB, 40.2a, 47.11b, 54.13a, 55.12a, 413.11a-14a; SS, 288.1a-1b; TZHDSL, 78.6a. CBD, 1, 657.</note>
